															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=301632&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250565" alt="Drewbear" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=301632)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;" >Drewbear</a></span> <span class="odate time_1407425005 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Aug 2014 15:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2083457">
									

<p>I like the idea of the Foundation building their own Vaults. And I know that the ease of access is in keeping with the games, but I just don't see the Foundation letting it be that easy. There are some weak spots, particularly the end with them just&#8230; accepting it and going straight back to what they were doing before finding the Vault. I'm also curious as to how O5-6 knows so much about the outside world, considering that the Vault was (theoretically) closed off from the outside world.</p>
<p>Still, nice use of Teddy, there.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Giving bearhugs to the unsuspecting since 1872.</p>

				</div>
					
					
