					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chrisakapiefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1578588); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1578588&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250565" alt="ChrisAKAPiefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1578588)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/chrisakapiefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1578588); return false;" >ChrisAKAPiefish</a></span> <span class="odate time_1407425845 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Aug 2014 15:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2083471">
									

<p>Yeah it's more as if the vault has fallen into disrepair somewhat like Aperture Science has at the beginning of Portal 2. I could possibly add in some hacking parts and I can understand that part but I think it was more of a shock on their part and that they likely will talk about it again (hence the eyebot)</p>
<p>O5-6 knowing about the outside world is more due to her being in a stasis like thing (Like Mr House) and being in control of eyebots used for scouting the wasteland and in my mind, the Foundation would still be able to gain access to feeds from robots like the securitrons.</p>
<p>Edit: Made some edits, nothing too major but hopefully it makes a little bit more sense now.</p>
<p>This is stuff I would explain into the tale but I found it difficult to find a place for them to fit. I will edit some parts to make more sense though :)</p>

							</div>

								
